{
  "stem": "521.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father went to academic high school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he-- he was living-- he was born and finished elementary school in a village.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he seemingly was a very bright boy, and they sent him to an academic high school after the four years of elementary school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Unfortunately, his parents were not very well-to-do, and he was living in a-- at a family who has taken him in during the year.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he had to go and eat, each and every day, at another Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it wasn't much fun, as he related to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after four years, he just said, he has had it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As a young boy, imagine 10 years old boy, who is living at-- at a strange Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And on top of this, if he wanted to eat, he had to go to a different Jewish family for seven days of the week.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, this wasn't really very encouraging for him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had a very what we called it a [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] is a kind of a Jewish family, which you would call a reformed Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother lit a candle on Fridays-- not necessarily on each and every Friday, whenever she remembered.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was brought up as-- as a Jew, as a good Jew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My grandfather was a very religious Jew, who was celebrating the coming and the going of the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my grandmother had a wig-- [INAUDIBLE] I thought it's ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If she had to shave her head, why to wear a wig?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is just a circum-- it has [? circum-going ?] of-- of the law, of the Jewish law.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So if you shave your head, then you should have your ha-- hair shaved.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But of course, at that time, I didn't think of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
